items.title: Chinese-owned Volvo Cars to cut 3,000 jobs
items.description: The firm's boss pointed to the "challenging period" faced by the industry as a reason for the layoffs.

items.title: Man charged over killing of Jordanian pilot burned alive by IS
items.description: Osama Krayem is accused of terrorism and war crimes in relation to the death of Moaz al-Kasasbeh.

items.title: Controversial US-backed group says it has begun aid distribution in Gaza
items.description: Hundreds of Palestinians collect food from a site run by the Gaza Humanitarian Foundation, whose work the UN calls a "distraction".

items.title: Ancient human fingerprint suggests Neanderthals made art
items.description: A Neanderthal man is believed to have painted a nose on a pebble using red pigment more than 43,000 years ago.

items.title: Trump administration seeks to pull estimated $100m in Harvard funding
items.description: Federal agencies will review their grants to Harvard to decide whether they should be terminated
